},{"text":"just how much love I need","start":34.36,"end":38.88},{"text":"All the love I leaned on","start":41.54,"end":47.84},{"text":"never filled the empty space","start":49.1,"end":53.38},{"text":"I was made for something more","start":55.48,"end":61.7},{"text":"something I don't have to chase","start":63.02,"end":67.32},{"text":"I was searching in the dark","start":69.3,"end":73.7},{"text":"for a love that wouldn't leave","start":74.38,"end":81.32},{"text":"How to know where love found me how to know where I","start":82.18,"end":93.46},{"text":"was free","start":93.46,"end":94.88},{"text":"How to know where all my shame was gone how to know","start":95.88,"end":104.86},{"text":"where I was finally home","start":104.86,"end":109.88},{"text":"How to know where mercy came","start":110.6,"end":115.9},{"text":"spoke my heart and called my name Right when I thought I","start":117.86,"end":127.3},{"text":"was too far gone","start":127.3,"end":130.44},{"text":"how to know where I was finally home","start":132.06,"end":137.32},{"text":"I had heard about his love but I thought it wasn't mine","start":138.04,"end":144.94},{"text":"But his words broke through my doubt","start":144.94,"end":148.72},{"text":"and his truth rewrote my life","start":149.48,"end":152.1},{"text":"Now a love I never knew","start":152.48,"end":155.66},{"text":"is alive inside my soul What I thought was out of reach","start":156.38,"end":162.5},{"text":"was right there all along Every wall I built inside started falling","start":163.2,"end":176.78},{"text":"one by one How to know where love found me how to","start":176.78,"end":188.44},{"text":"know where I was free","start":188.44,"end":193.06},{"text":"How to know where all my shame was gone how to know","start":194.06,"end":202.82},{"text":"where I was finally home","start":202.82,"end":207.58},{"text":"His grace paved the path","start":208.28,"end":211.76},{"text":"his mercy pulled me through His sacrifice paid the cost","start":212.72,"end":218.76},{"text":"so I could start brand new His grace his mercy his sacrifice","start":219.14,"end":227.72},{"text":"his love Is calling out your name saying you are enough How","start":228.0,"end":240.66},{"text":"to know where love found me how to know where I was","start":240.66,"end":251.24},{"text":"free","start":251.24,"end":252.18},{"text":"How to know where all my shame was gone","start":253.2,"end":260.64},{"text":"how to know where I was finally home How to know where","start":261.3,"end":269.78},{"text":"chains fell off how to know where I was lost and found","start":269.78,"end":280.48},{"text":"Right when I thought it was all over","start":280.58,"end":287.2},{"text":"how to know where love came down","start":289.28,"end":293.78},{"text":"How to know where you can't be found how to know where","start":295.4,"end":306.58},{"text":"grace comes down","start":306.58,"end":308.64}],"duration":308.64,"plain_text":"Life's road has been long, full of twists I couldn't see I was scared to admit, just how much love I need All the love I leaned on, never filled the empty space I was made for something more, something I don't have to chase I was searching in the dark, for a love that wouldn't leave How to know where love found me, how to know where I was free How to know where all my shame was gone, how to know where I was finally home How to know where mercy came, spoke my heart and called my name Right when I thought I was too far gone, how to know where I was finally home I had heard about his love, but I thought it wasn't mine But his words broke through my doubt, and his truth rewrote my life Now a love I never knew, is alive inside my soul What I thought was out of reach, was right there all along Every wall I built inside, started falling one by one How to know where love found me, how to know where I was free How to know where all my shame was gone, how to know where I was finally home His grace paved the path, his mercy pulled me through His sacrifice paid the cost, so I could start brand new His grace, his mercy, his sacrifice, his love Is calling out your name, saying you are enough How to know where love found me, how to know where I was free How to know where all my shame was gone, how to know where I was finally home How to know where chains fell off, how to know where I was lost and found Right when I thought it was all over, how to know where love came down How to know where you can't be found, how to know where grace comes down"}